@@yTestimony@@W is the Sentinel's class-specific combat resource — marks
accumulated on a single target through successful defensive reading.

@@yBuilding Testimony:@@W
  * @@wDodge, Parry, or Block@@W: +1 mark per successful avoidance.
  * @@wRead Opponent@@W (skill): instantly grants +2 marks.
  * @@wPassive tick@@W: +1 mark every 3 combat rounds against the same target.
  * @@wMeasured Response@@W procs: +1 mark on counter-attack.
  * @@wNinth Descent@@W (buff): doubles all testimony gain for 4 rounds.
  * Cap: @@w9 marks@@W maximum.

@@yLosing Testimony:@@W
  * @@wTarget switch@@W: resets to 0 (observations are specific to one foe).
  * @@wTarget death@@W: resets to 0.
  * @@wStun@@W: lose half marks (rounded down). @@wSeal Testimony@@W reduces
    this to losing only 1 mark.
  * @@wFlee/recall@@W: resets to 0.
  * @@wOut of combat@@W: decays by 1 per tick (not instant reset).

@@ySpending Testimony:@@W
  * Use the @@wverdict@@W command to consume all marks for a single strike.
  * Damage multiplier and secondary effects scale with marks spent.
  * After verdict, a 2-round cooldown before testimony accumulates again.

@@yKey difference from other resources:@@W
  * Chi (Monk) builds on @@woffense@@W — +1 per successful attack.
  * Combo (Warden) builds on @@wvaried offense@@W — auto-finisher when full.
  * Testimony builds on @@wdefense@@W — +1 per avoidance, spend when ready.

See also: @@mverdict sentinel ninth descent seal testimony read opponent@@W
